analysisPopulations.name: Intent-to-Treat Population
analysisPopulations.text: The ITT population is defined as all randomized patients, whether or not the patient has received the assigned study treatment.
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The ITT population is defined as all randomized patients, whether or not the patient has received the assigned study treatment.

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic-Evaluable Population
analysisPopulations.text: The pharmacokinetic (PK)-evaluable population is defined as all patients who received any dose of study treatment and who have at least one post-baseline PK sample available.
analysisPopulations.label: PK-Evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The pharmacokinetic (PK)-evaluable population is defined as all patients who received any dose of study treatment and who have at least one post-baseline PK sample available.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received any dose of study treatment AND has >=1 post-baseline PK sample

analysisPopulations.name: PRO-Evaluable Population
analysisPopulations.text: The patient-reported outcome (PRO)-evaluable population will include all randomized patients who have a baseline and at least 1 post-baseline assessment.
analysisPopulations.label: PRO-Evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The patient-reported outcome (PRO)-evaluable population will include all randomized patients who have a baseline and at least 1 post-baseline assessment.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND has baseline assessment AND has >=1 post-baseline assessment

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Population
analysisPopulations.text: The safety population consists of all randomized patients who received at least one full or partial dose of any study treatment, with patients grouped according to the actual treatment received.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The safety population consists of all randomized patients who received at least one full or partial dose of any study treatment, with patients grouped according to the actual treatment received.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 full or partial dose of study treatment

analysisPopulations.name: Anti-Drug-Antibody-Evaluable Population
analysisPopulations.text: The anti-drug-antibody (ADA)-evaluable population is defined as all patients who received any dose of atezolizumab and who have at least one post-baseline ADA assessment.
analysisPopulations.label: ADA-Evaluable
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The anti-drug-antibody (ADA)-evaluable population is defined as all patients who received any dose of atezolizumab and who have at least one post-baseline ADA assessment.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received any dose of atezolizumab AND has >=1 post-baseline ADA assessment

characteristics.name: ECOG Performance Status
characteristics.description: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Performance Status (0 vs. 1)
